direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods are part of the Map.Entry interface and are used to compare and hash entries, respectively.
The hashCode method depends on the key returned by getKey() for its computation.
The hashCode method depends on the value returned by getValue() for its computation.
Both methods involve processing the key and value of the entry, although for different purposes (string representation vs. hashing).
Both methods interact with the underlying map to retrieve or modify the value associated with the key.
